<i>♪ He made his fortune</i>
<i>of being idle ♪</i>

01:33.268 --> 01:37.600
<i>♪ Catching fish until the dusk ♪</i>

01:39.538 --> 01:43.903
<i>♪ I couldn't live outside</i>
<i>of city walls ♪</i>

01:43.938 --> 01:48.149
<i>♪ So scared of</i>
<i>getting in alone ♪</i>

01:49.878 --> 01:52.615
<i>♪ And oh, oh, oh ♪</i>

01:52.650 --> 01:54.947
<i>♪ If I could go back in time ♪</i>

01:54.982 --> 01:59.556
<i>♪ I know that I will try</i>
<i>and change his mind ♪</i>

01:59.591 --> 02:01.723
I know most people
go to Rome or Venice,

02:01.758 --> 02:03.329
I am not those people.

02:03.364 --> 02:04.825
<i> I'm just saying,</i>
<i>you can't go</i>

02:04.860 --> 02:06.959
all the way to Italy
and not see the Colosseum.

02:06.994 --> 02:10.303
Any place that was good enough
for Oscar Wilde or D.H. Lawrence

02:10.338 --> 02:11.733
is good enough for me.

02:11.768 --> 02:14.208
Yeah, I don't know who
any of those people are.

02:14.243 --> 02:15.671
<i>Never mind.</i>

02:15.706 --> 02:18.476
Wait, Oscar Wilde,
didn't he write that book?

02:18.511 --> 02:20.214
-Famous playwright.
-<i> Anyway,</i>

02:20.249 --> 02:22.645
just promise me you'll at least
check out Venice.

02:22.680 --> 02:23.943
<i>I think it will be</i>
<i>really good for you.</i>

02:23.978 --> 02:25.681
Well, I just, I just wanted
to let you know

02:25.716 --> 02:27.782
-that I made it.
-<i> Hurry back,</i>

02:27.817 --> 02:29.421
I'm pulling double duty
at the shop.

02:29.456 --> 02:30.620
Ooh, yeah, about that, I think

02:30.655 --> 02:31.852
I might just stay here forever.

02:31.887 --> 02:33.293
So plan accordingly.

02:33.328 --> 02:35.559
Yeah. Yeah.

02:35.594 --> 02:37.264
Hey, Hal?

02:37.299 --> 02:40.861
I'm really proud of you
for what you wrote.

02:40.896 --> 02:43.963
<i>-People are still</i>
<i>talking about it.</i>
-Hey, we're pulling in now.

02:43.998 --> 02:46.504
Uh, give Stella a kiss.
I'll talk to you, all right?

02:46.539 --> 02:50.541
All right, man. Well, be good
or be good at it.

02:50.576 --> 02:52.741
Will do. Later.

02:52.776 --> 02:54.380
<i>♪ ...change his mind ♪</i>

02:54.415 --> 02:58.582
<i>♪ I know this time ♪</i>

02:58.617 --> 03:02.355
<i>♪ This time I won't be mad ♪</i>

03:46.401 --> 03:47.961
Okay, Mr. Flynn,

03:47.996 --> 03:49.600
uh, single room?

03:49.635 --> 03:51.965
Uh, do you have, uh,
a double or something?

03:52.000 --> 03:53.901
-But you are single.
-Yeah,

03:53.936 --> 03:55.507
but I mean,
you don't have anything bigger?

03:55.542 --> 03:56.937
Like<i> piu grande,</i> or?

03:56.972 --> 03:59.038
You are two person?

03:59.073 --> 04:02.613
No, I am-- It's just me, but...

04:02.648 --> 04:05.880
Then the single room is good.

04:05.915 --> 04:08.355
Okay. Great. Single room it is.
Thank you.

04:08.390 --> 04:09.818
<i>Perfecto.</i>

04:09.853 --> 04:11.325
<i>Perfecto.</i>

04:11.360 --> 04:12.722
You're welcome.

04:38.585 --> 04:39.650
Huh.

05:16.425 --> 05:20.922
<i>♪ The leaves are changing</i>
<i>now that summer's gone ♪</i>

05:20.957 --> 05:26.829
<i>♪ And all the city folks rush ♪</i>

05:26.864 --> 05:31.537
<i>♪ Sometimes I wonder why</i>
<i>he's doing that ♪</i>

05:31.572 --> 05:36.707
<i>♪ If you see him say hello ♪</i>

05:36.742 --> 05:39.644
<i>♪ And oh, oh, oh ♪</i>

05:39.679 --> 05:42.713
<i>♪ If I could go back in time ♪</i>

05:42.748 --> 05:47.718
<i>♪ I know that I will try</i>
<i>change his mind ♪</i>

05:47.753 --> 05:52.888
<i>♪ I know this time ♪</i>

05:52.923 --> 05:58.025
<i>♪ I know this time ♪</i>

05:58.060 --> 06:02.634
<i>♪ I know ♪</i>

06:02.669 --> 06:07.540
<i>♪ Oh, this time I'll love you ♪</i>

06:21.182 --> 06:22.951
Oh, I'm not playing
for tips.

06:22.986 --> 06:24.183
It's just for fun.

06:25.619 --> 06:28.990
That's a great cover.
It sound eerily close
to the original song.

06:29.025 --> 06:30.090
I'd hope so.

06:30.125 --> 06:31.663
You take any requests?

06:31.698 --> 06:34.028
Nope, I only play originals.

06:34.063 --> 06:35.634
Well, yeah, but...

06:38.034 --> 06:39.506
Oh, wow.

06:39.541 --> 06:41.475
Okay, yeah,
I feel like an idiot.

06:41.510 --> 06:43.906
Here I am offering five euros
to famous musician.

06:43.941 --> 06:46.579
Oh, that's a bit of a stretch.
I'm not famous.

06:46.614 --> 06:48.944
Oh, wow. You're Josie Day.

06:48.979 --> 06:50.847
-I think so.

06:50.882 --> 06:55.852
Wow. I am Hal. Hal--
Hal Flynn. Just wow.

06:55.887 --> 06:59.592
Stop saying wow.
Wait, you're not one of those
cruise ship people, are you?

06:59.627 --> 07:01.187
-I'm sorry?
-How'd you get here?

07:01.222 --> 07:04.025
Planes, trains and automobiles,
in that order, actually.

07:04.060 --> 07:05.829
You know, you missed
tourist season.

07:05.864 --> 07:06.929
It, like, just ended.

07:06.964 --> 07:08.634
No. I'm not a tourist.

07:08.669 --> 07:10.570
You're definitely not a local.

07:10.605 --> 07:13.540
Well, I'm not here
to do touristy things.

07:13.575 --> 07:16.202
Then what are you here for?

07:16.237 --> 07:18.644
Hmm.

07:18.679 --> 07:21.911
Hate to interrupt your playing,
but would you do me a courtesy

07:21.946 --> 07:24.045
and take my photo,
just like this?

07:24.080 --> 07:27.180
Courtesy? Why, yes, sir.

07:27.215 --> 07:29.655
Oh. Beautiful. Who is she?

07:31.923 --> 07:34.858
There you go.

07:34.893 --> 07:37.124
Well, let me do you one better.

07:37.159 --> 07:39.225
This was definitely not
shot on an iPhone,

07:39.260 --> 07:41.964
and I happen to know a cute,
little Mom and Pop shop

07:41.999 --> 07:44.197
down the road that
still develops. Can I?

07:44.232 --> 07:46.298
Uh, yeah, sure.
But if you can still

07:46.333 --> 07:48.201
get one on the phone too,
if you don't mind?

07:48.236 --> 07:50.577
Yeah. Of course.

07:50.612 --> 07:52.513
-I think she stood there.
-Okay.

07:59.346 --> 08:02.050
Okay.

08:02.085 --> 08:04.019
So I take it
you've been here before,

08:04.054 --> 08:05.559
uh, Taormina?

08:05.594 --> 08:07.088
-Once or twice.

08:07.123 --> 08:09.794
Well, I've been in Sicily
for a couple of hours

08:09.829 --> 08:11.994
and I haven't eaten
which is a cardinal sin

08:12.029 --> 08:14.700
if I am not mistaken.
Uh, any recommendations?

08:14.735 --> 08:17.703
-You wanna know a secret?
-Of course.

08:17.738 --> 08:19.936
Wander into any one
of these places

08:19.971 --> 08:22.576
and you will have
the best pasta and wine

08:22.611 --> 08:24.611
you've had in
you're entire life.

08:24.646 --> 08:26.844
-Hmm.

08:26.879 --> 08:29.781
-And there we go.

08:29.816 --> 08:31.178
Think I got a few good ones.

08:31.213 --> 08:32.982
-Great.
-Your stuff.

08:33.017 --> 08:35.886
Thanks. Um...

08:35.921 --> 08:39.923
thank you for the...
the photo and the song. I'm...

08:39.958 --> 08:42.959
-I'm a fan.
-Of course.

08:42.994 --> 08:44.323
Uh...

08:52.201 --> 08:53.332
Hey, Hal?

09:06.314 --> 09:07.984
This place is pretty dead.

09:08.019 --> 09:09.656
Yeah, people don't go out
till late here.

09:09.691 --> 09:11.724
Restaurants don't even
open until- 00.

09:11.759 --> 09:13.154
Ugh, I'd wither away.

09:13.189 --> 09:15.255
Where are you staying?

09:15.290 --> 09:16.630
Uh, Hotel Victoria.

09:16.665 --> 09:18.390
Mm, Oscar Wilde.

09:18.425 --> 09:20.161
Precisely, how'd you know?

09:20.196 --> 09:22.328
Oh, they put signs around
for the tourists.

09:22.363 --> 09:25.298
Mm. This is seriously amazing.

09:25.333 --> 09:26.904
Oh!

09:26.939 --> 09:30.303
-So you're a writer?
-Uh...

09:30.338 --> 09:32.074
That's a pretty big leap.

09:32.109 --> 09:34.208
You're not here
for touristy things,

09:34.243 --> 09:37.310
you're staying at
the Hotel Victoria,

09:37.345 --> 09:41.050
-you carry around this notebook.
-Okay, okay. Sure.

09:41.085 --> 09:43.382
Not a writer, but more,
um, aspiring.

09:43.417 --> 09:45.087
So you're modest.

09:45.122 --> 09:46.858
No, realistic. I enjoy it,

09:46.893 --> 09:49.058
but there are just
so many out there that--

09:49.093 --> 09:52.292
Mm. This is seriously
life-changing. It's-- it's--

09:52.327 --> 09:54.866
-What you got?
-I think it was a Tagliatelle.

09:54.901 --> 09:58.166
No, I mean your notebook.
Read me something.

09:58.201 --> 09:59.431
What, now?

09:59.466 --> 10:03.204
No, in 15 minutes.
I'll set a timer.

10:03.239 --> 10:04.436
Yes, now.

10:04.471 --> 10:06.042
No way,
you're a famous musician.

10:06.077 --> 10:08.341
Oh, my gosh.
I am not a famous musician.

10:08.376 --> 10:10.244
I have one semi well-known song,

10:10.279 --> 10:11.751
and nothing since.

10:11.786 --> 10:13.313
And nobody even knows
who I am

10:13.348 --> 10:15.183
except for you, apparently.

10:15.218 --> 10:16.921
Okay. People know who you are.

10:16.956 --> 10:21.387
Hal, I'm getting impatient.

10:21.422 --> 10:24.896
Okay, fine. I have this...
this poem of the day.

10:24.931 --> 10:27.393
It's stupid short stuff, but--

10:27.428 --> 10:29.230
Sounds perfect.

10:32.301 --> 10:34.301
Normally, I wouldn't
share these with anyone.

10:34.336 --> 10:37.337
Well, normally,
you wouldn't be in Taormina.

10:37.372 --> 10:39.713
Okay. But you have to
promise me something.

10:39.748 --> 10:42.276
Okay. You can't do that thing
where you pretend to like it

10:42.311 --> 10:44.080
even if you don't, okay?
I'll know.

10:47.250 --> 10:49.250
Why are you not talking?
It's just making me
even more nervous.

10:49.285 --> 10:50.416
Hal, you're stalling.

10:50.451 --> 10:53.386
Oh, gosh, okay.

10:53.421 --> 10:54.387
Um...

10:57.293 --> 10:59.359
"I waltz through this wave
of strangers.

10:59.394 --> 11:01.229
Their conversations,

11:01.264 --> 11:05.002
they topple over each other
and it sounds somewhat like,

11:05.037 --> 11:06.333
well, like rain.

11:06.368 --> 11:09.138
For now, I'm lost
and well, that's okay.

11:09.173 --> 11:10.942
See, I'm happiest when I'm lost

11:10.977 --> 11:13.879
because I learn to be
happy with myself.

11:13.914 --> 11:15.815
I'm reminded
of a thought though,

11:15.850 --> 11:19.049
of the time
my parents were children too.

11:19.084 --> 11:22.481
On the topic of children,
there they are over there,

11:22.516 --> 11:24.758
a few playing soccer
on the piazza,

11:24.793 --> 11:26.518
two restaurant chairs
as their goal

11:26.553 --> 11:28.058
and that's enough for now.

11:29.930 --> 11:31.996
The town is big
while they're small,

11:32.031 --> 11:34.493
it will grow small
as they grow taller.

11:34.528 --> 11:37.837
And, hey, it really does.
You're right.

11:37.872 --> 11:40.840
The sun shines differently here

11:40.875 --> 11:41.874
effervescent bright."

11:46.815 --> 11:48.342
-Hal, I need you to look at me.
-Nope.

11:50.544 --> 11:51.477
Right this instant.

11:55.318 --> 11:58.022
-You're good.
-You promise you wouldn't--

11:58.057 --> 11:58.957
You're good.

12:01.962 --> 12:04.358
-You're just being nice.
-No.

12:04.393 --> 12:06.228
But I am a little buzzed.

12:06.263 --> 12:09.495
And that jet lag
is not gonna cure itself.

12:09.530 --> 12:11.134
You should get some sleep.

12:11.169 --> 12:12.806
Of course. Right.

12:12.841 --> 12:13.972
Do you want me to walk you?

12:16.207 --> 12:17.437
Yeah, I'd like that.

12:20.277 --> 12:22.915
Could I have your coaster?

12:22.950 --> 12:23.850
Sure.

12:25.920 --> 12:26.820
<i>Grazie.</i>

12:36.293 --> 12:40.559
Oscar Wilde arrived
in Taormina in 1898.

12:40.594 --> 12:42.066
Well, there you have it.

12:42.101 --> 12:44.035
Uh, I'll get these photos
to you tomorrow?

12:44.070 --> 12:45.333
Who needs the time, thank you.

12:45.368 --> 12:47.005
Should we meet at the fountain
at four?

12:47.040 --> 12:49.436
Uh, yeah, I think I should be
awake by then.

12:51.638 --> 12:53.880
Okay. Here.

12:56.181 --> 12:58.214
Hmm.

12:58.249 --> 13:00.282
All right. Think I have
a little something here.

13:04.486 --> 13:07.058
There you go.

13:07.093 --> 13:11.128
"To now,
the memory of tomorrow."

13:11.163 --> 13:13.196
Hey, so, should we exchange
numbers or something?

13:13.231 --> 13:15.066
Just in case, you know,
anything comes up or--

13:15.101 --> 13:19.268
Let's do this
the old fashioned way,
Mr. Oscar Wilde.

13:19.303 --> 13:22.502
We have a time and a place
and I'll be there.

13:22.537 --> 13:24.009
<i>-Buona sera.</i>
<i>-Buona sera.</i>

13:24.044 --> 13:25.637
<i>-Anche tu.</i>
<i>-Gesundheit.</i>

13:25.672 --> 13:28.145
-Hey, you better show up.

13:28.180 --> 13:29.311
Oh, I'll show up.

14:34.345 --> 14:38.281
<i>♪ To now ♪</i>

14:40.351 --> 14:44.188
<i>♪ To now ♪</i>

14:44.223 --> 14:46.685
<i>♪ It's the memory ♪</i>

14:48.557 --> 14:51.624
<i>♪ Of tomorrow ♪</i>

15:16.618 --> 15:19.388
You're early.

15:19.423 --> 15:21.225
-You're early.

15:21.260 --> 15:24.261
Well, I wanted to get here
before you got here.

15:24.296 --> 15:25.328
Me, too, I guess.

15:25.363 --> 15:27.396
Okay. So, don't be mad,

15:27.431 --> 15:29.365
but the photos
aren't quite ready yet.

15:29.400 --> 15:31.565
-Oh, that's fine.
-But they said
they can get them done

15:31.600 --> 15:33.732
in like, two or three days.
When do you leave again?

15:33.767 --> 15:36.075
Uh, I'm here for a week.

15:36.110 --> 15:39.408
Quick question. What are these,
like extra, extra small or--

15:39.443 --> 15:41.674
That's how they do it here.
It's an Americano.

15:41.709 --> 15:43.577
This is as big as it comes.

15:45.284 --> 15:46.580
Quality over quantity.

15:46.615 --> 15:48.483
Yeah.

15:48.518 --> 15:50.584
Okay. Let's go.
I wanna show you something.

15:50.619 --> 15:53.092
Is it the Greek theater?
I wanna see it so bad.

15:53.127 --> 15:55.325
I though you said
you weren't a tourist, Hal.

15:55.360 --> 15:57.129
-What do you mean?
-Okay. Well, yeah,

15:57.164 --> 15:58.559
we could go wait in line

15:58.594 --> 16:01.331
and we can listen
to tour guides ramble on and on,

16:01.366 --> 16:04.433
but I really wanted to show you
one of the best views
in Taormina.

16:04.468 --> 16:06.105
-Okay, fine.
-Okay.

16:06.140 --> 16:07.238
Let's go.

16:27.260 --> 16:30.261
Hey, uh, quick question.

16:30.296 --> 16:32.296
Are you taking me
to Narnia or what?

16:32.331 --> 16:34.760
Okay. It is right up here.

16:34.795 --> 16:37.103
You told me it is
the best view of Taormina

16:37.138 --> 16:38.599
and I'm training
for a triathlon, Josie.

16:38.634 --> 16:40.469
Oh, you are fine.

16:45.608 --> 16:47.707
This is-- this is
just incredible.

16:47.742 --> 16:50.248
Told you.

16:50.283 --> 16:52.085
Hey, what's that?

16:52.120 --> 16:53.317
It's a little turn of phrase.

16:53.352 --> 16:55.418
-Poem of the day?
-Maybe.

16:55.453 --> 16:57.420
Okay, well, share.

16:57.455 --> 16:59.719
-No, no way you're putting me
through that again.
-Come on.

16:59.754 --> 17:02.128
Well--
I just started. All right?

17:02.163 --> 17:03.459
Maybe a little bit later.

17:03.494 --> 17:05.131
-Okay, I'll hold you to that.
-Yeah.

17:05.166 --> 17:08.662
If you won't share, I will.

17:08.697 --> 17:10.829
-Really?
-Mm-hmm.

17:10.864 --> 17:16.340
I cooked up this little melody
last night.

17:16.375 --> 17:18.738
Might sound familiar.

17:18.773 --> 17:21.477
Okay. I much prefer to be
on this side of things,
by the way.

17:21.512 --> 17:22.643
Shut up.

17:26.319 --> 17:28.220
-Uh, there's no chorus.
-Okay.

17:28.255 --> 17:29.716
No chorus yet.
Just the verse.

17:31.522 --> 17:34.325
<i>♪ To now ♪</i>

17:36.230 --> 17:38.890
<i>♪ To now ♪</i>

17:38.925 --> 17:44.269
<i>♪ It's the memory of tomorrow ♪</i>

17:44.304 --> 17:49.109
<i>♪ The memory of tomorrow ♪</i>

18:00.749 --> 18:02.584
-Why'd you stop?
-I don't know,

18:02.619 --> 18:04.586
hearing it again,
it's no good.

18:04.621 --> 18:06.456
Are you kidding me?

18:06.491 --> 18:07.919
No, it's no good.

18:07.954 --> 18:10.163
Josie, look at me.

18:10.198 --> 18:11.263
You're good.

18:13.861 --> 18:17.236
-No. Back to the drawing board.
-Ugh, you're out of your mind.

18:19.471 --> 18:21.834
It was really good though.

18:21.869 --> 18:23.209
I mean, I wrote it, so...

18:25.906 --> 18:27.279
I want 50 percent.

18:28.744 --> 18:30.183
You'll get 49.

18:40.426 --> 18:41.788
How'd it go?

18:41.823 --> 18:44.263
<i>♪ To now ♪</i>

18:44.298 --> 18:47.464
<i>-♪ The memory of tomorrow ♪</i>
-Okay.

18:47.499 --> 18:48.894
Is that how it went?

18:48.929 --> 18:51.204
-It's close. It's close.
-It was good. I liked it.

18:51.239 --> 18:53.206
-I thought it was pretty good.
-Lived it better

18:53.241 --> 18:55.274
Well, I'm this way.

18:55.309 --> 18:56.902
I'm that.

18:56.937 --> 18:59.674
Look, Hal, I know you didn't
come all the way to Sicily

18:59.709 --> 19:01.775
-to hang out with me.
-I didn't?

19:01.810 --> 19:04.448
But if you're free tomorrow,

19:04.483 --> 19:06.516
I do happen to know
a cool spot.

19:06.551 --> 19:08.881
And I still have to
get you those photos.

19:08.916 --> 19:11.752
Let's see, tomorrow,
I'm doing a lot of
wandering around,

19:11.787 --> 19:14.392
um, just staring off
into the distance aimlessly.

19:14.427 --> 19:15.888
Yeah. I think tomorrow
could work.

19:15.923 --> 19:17.362
Should we finally exchange info?

19:19.498 --> 19:22.763
Um, no. Old-fashioned.

19:22.798 --> 19:24.567
Then we need a time and place.

19:24.602 --> 19:27.834
Let's do... noon at my hotel.

19:27.869 --> 19:29.440
You better show up.

19:29.475 --> 19:31.937
-Well, yeah, I'll show up.

19:31.972 --> 19:34.643
<i>-Buona sera.</i>
<i>-Anche tu.</i>

19:34.678 --> 19:36.711
-Very good.
-Thank you.

19:36.746 --> 19:39.010
Oh, hey, I finished it,
by the way.

19:39.045 --> 19:41.287
The poem, it's called "Luca."
You want to...

19:43.984 --> 19:47.722
"From here, I saw hundreds
of honey-gold street lamps.

19:47.757 --> 19:49.592
They were tripled
along the stones,

19:49.627 --> 19:51.726
hundreds, but I only
thought of one.

19:51.761 --> 19:55.928
A trail of blue
fogged by the smoke
of Signore Lucas Monticarlo.

19:55.963 --> 19:58.931
He smirked as two young lovers
shared their first kiss.

19:58.966 --> 20:00.702
A first, he knew,

20:00.737 --> 20:03.738
for both said 'Whew'
right after.

20:03.773 --> 20:06.642
He lowered his eyes
to his wing tip
olive-green shoes,

20:06.677 --> 20:08.446
and blinked.

20:08.481 --> 20:10.712
That blink was a minute
and that minute turned two.

20:10.747 --> 20:14.320
Tomorrow turned yesterday
and time already flew.

20:14.355 --> 20:18.324
The boy was him and this day
when they first met,

20:18.359 --> 20:19.886
he recalled how he missed her

20:19.921 --> 20:21.690
and she wasn't even gone yet."

20:24.024 --> 20:26.860
Such a cool guy, huh?

20:26.895 --> 20:27.894
If you say so.

21:29.562 --> 21:30.858
Come on, keep up.

21:30.893 --> 21:32.123
Come-- Oh, yeah.

21:32.158 --> 21:33.828
Where the hell
did you come from?

21:39.000 --> 21:42.375
So this is one of
my favorite spots to write,
in all of Taormina.

21:42.410 --> 21:44.377
Anyone can come here,
free of charge,

21:44.412 --> 21:46.478
and just enjoy the scenery
and ruins.

21:46.513 --> 21:49.547
And there is the amphitheater,
it's right up there.

21:49.582 --> 21:52.110
Oh, my goodness. This is crazy.

21:52.145 --> 21:54.651
I mean, I never read anything
about this place.

21:54.686 --> 21:56.686
Sounds like you need
a good tour guide.

21:56.721 --> 21:58.523
Well, it looks like
I found one.

22:23.880 --> 22:25.979
Mm-mm-mm.

22:26.014 --> 22:27.948
Another ten out of ten
on the cuisine.

22:27.983 --> 22:30.082
I mean, do they have
bad food around here?

22:30.117 --> 22:32.051
If there is, I haven't found it.

22:32.086 --> 22:33.921
Oh, my gosh.
And the architecture.

22:33.956 --> 22:35.087
I mean, you have this--

22:35.122 --> 22:36.858
this ancient Roman sculpture

22:36.893 --> 22:38.761
right next to a building
with all these new additions.

22:38.796 --> 22:41.896
-I mean, it's nuts.
-Greek.

22:41.931 --> 22:43.634
-I'm sorry?
-Well,

22:43.669 --> 22:45.438
it was Greek for five centuries

22:45.473 --> 22:47.440
before the Romans came over.

22:47.475 --> 22:48.903
So you know a lot
about this stuff.

22:48.938 --> 22:51.202
-I've overheard a lot of
tour guides.
-Well...

22:51.237 --> 22:52.841
I mean, you go to a place
like Boston

22:52.876 --> 22:55.877
and they're just so reverent
with the history.

22:55.912 --> 22:58.649
But here, it's sort of like
they can pay respects

22:58.684 --> 23:01.146
without being too precious.

23:01.181 --> 23:02.917
I never thought about it
like that.

23:02.952 --> 23:05.854
It's just like you said.
Perfect blend of old and new.

23:05.889 --> 23:08.153
Ah. All right.

23:08.188 --> 23:09.858
Oh, before I forget.

23:12.797 --> 23:14.797
Oh, my gosh.

23:14.832 --> 23:16.535
All right. Inspection time.

23:19.639 --> 23:21.804
Wow. You weren't lying.

23:21.839 --> 23:24.235
These do beat the hell
out of a...
out of a phone picture.

23:24.270 --> 23:26.644
-I told you.
-Thank you.

23:26.679 --> 23:27.579
You're welcome.

23:31.013 --> 23:33.651
So, Hal, I've been thinking.

23:33.686 --> 23:35.851
Uh-oh.

23:35.886 --> 23:38.183
-We both are here to write.
-Well, I don't know
if that's exactly--

23:38.218 --> 23:41.087
And I find you interesting.

23:41.122 --> 23:44.662
So I was thinking that...

23:44.697 --> 23:45.762
You know what?

23:45.797 --> 23:47.093
It'd be easier
if I just showed you.

23:47.128 --> 23:48.765
Come on. Let's go.

23:48.800 --> 23:50.866
What-- What?
There's so much good food left.

23:50.901 --> 23:52.967
There's plenty more
where that came from.

23:53.002 --> 23:54.001
All right.

23:55.972 --> 23:58.137
What's with the coaster thing?

23:58.172 --> 24:00.073
By themselves,
just flimsy cardboard,

24:00.108 --> 24:02.515
but a little chicken scratch,
they become mementos.

24:02.550 --> 24:03.879
You know it's weird, right?

24:03.914 --> 24:04.979
It's normal, right?

24:41.248 --> 24:44.183
-This is where you're staying?
-Yep.

24:44.218 --> 24:46.053
Oh, my God!

24:48.728 --> 24:50.222
I am sorry.

24:50.257 --> 24:52.763
I did not know you were
roughing it like this.

24:52.798 --> 24:54.259
-You're hilarious.
-No, I mean,

24:54.294 --> 24:56.096
I seriously would have offered
any assistance.

24:56.131 --> 24:57.966
I mean, are you okay?
Do you need me to call someone?

24:58.001 --> 25:00.166
-I'm laughing on the inside.
-Oh, here's actually--

25:00.201 --> 25:02.102
here are those euros
I offered you before.

25:02.137 --> 25:03.675
Just take them all.
I mean, you need them

25:03.710 --> 25:05.545
more than I do. You know? I--

25:13.115 --> 25:14.015
Wow.

25:18.186 --> 25:19.988
Uh...

25:20.023 --> 25:21.990
I'm speechless.

25:22.025 --> 25:24.355
How much does a place
like this go for?

25:24.390 --> 25:26.962
Sorry, inappropriate question.
None of my business.

25:26.997 --> 25:30.163
No, honestly, I have no idea.
My boyfriend's parents
bought it a few years back.

25:34.873 --> 25:36.136
Oh.

25:36.171 --> 25:37.973
I guess I forgot
to mention that.

25:38.008 --> 25:41.713
That's a pretty big thing
to forget.

25:41.748 --> 25:44.617
Look, I think
you should stay here
for the rest of your trip.

25:44.652 --> 25:46.850
Wait. What? Okay, back it up.

25:46.885 --> 25:48.720
I know it's not exactly
in Taormina,

25:48.755 --> 25:50.216
but there's so much
cool stuff here.

25:50.251 --> 25:52.284
The real non-touristy
kind of stuff.

25:52.319 --> 25:54.121
And plus, you could save money
on your hotel.

25:54.156 --> 25:56.057
There's so many things
wrong with this idea.

25:56.092 --> 25:57.795
-I don't see any problem.
-Okay.

25:57.830 --> 25:58.829
Uh, let's see. Uh,

25:58.865 --> 26:00.633
What about the boyfriend
I just found out about?

26:00.668 --> 26:01.667
-What about him?
-I don't think

26:01.702 --> 26:02.833
he'd like the idea

26:02.868 --> 26:04.329
of a strange man with you

26:04.364 --> 26:05.638
in his parents' villa.

26:05.673 --> 26:06.705
He doesn't have to know.

26:09.908 --> 26:11.677
I need to process this.

26:11.712 --> 26:13.371
Look, Hal, I don't even know
what's going on.

26:13.406 --> 26:15.208
We were supposed to go
to Switzerland together,

26:15.243 --> 26:17.309
and then we got in
this big fight,

26:17.344 --> 26:19.982
and he left and we had
a falling out.

26:20.017 --> 26:21.687
He left you quite the bail here.

26:21.722 --> 26:23.216
There's so much space here
to spread out and write,

26:23.251 --> 26:25.086
we might not even
see each other.

26:25.121 --> 26:26.351
I don't know. It doesn't seem--

26:26.386 --> 26:27.891
Can it just be what it is?

26:27.926 --> 26:30.157
Depends on exactly what it is.

26:30.192 --> 26:31.928
A writers retreat.

26:31.963 --> 26:34.832
A perfectly innocent
writers retreat.

26:34.867 --> 26:36.295
Two friends hanging out,

26:36.330 --> 26:39.133
looking for inspiration
and writing.

26:39.168 --> 26:41.399
Sounds more like you are
convincing yourself here.

26:41.434 --> 26:44.270
I like spending time with you.

26:44.305 --> 26:47.438
Do you like spending time
with me?

26:47.473 --> 26:49.308
-Yes.
-Then it's settled.

26:49.343 --> 26:50.947
Writers retreat.

26:50.982 --> 26:53.917
-You're very bossy.
-Thank you.

26:55.921 --> 26:57.822
Why do I feel like
we're gonna regret this?

27:00.761 --> 27:03.157
Ah.<i> Grazie,</i> Signori.

27:03.192 --> 27:05.390
-Beautiful.
-Arrivederci, signor Flynn.

27:05.425 --> 27:06.732
<i>Grazie.</i>

27:28.789 --> 27:30.283
Comfortable?

27:30.318 --> 27:31.988
Uh, are you kidding?

27:32.023 --> 27:33.891
I, I feel like a king.

27:33.926 --> 27:35.387
Good.

27:35.422 --> 27:37.895
Um, I'll have to show you
how to make the coffee.

27:37.930 --> 27:39.765
Here, they do it differently.
Moka pot.

27:39.800 --> 27:41.899
But other than that,
make yourself at home.

27:41.934 --> 27:44.429
Okay. Um, well, this is nuts.

27:44.464 --> 27:46.431
-Uh, but thank you.
-Of course.

27:46.466 --> 27:48.807
Wait till you see the view
we have for sunset.

27:48.842 --> 27:52.206
-It gets better than this?
-Yes.

27:52.241 --> 27:53.911
Okay.

28:06.321 --> 28:08.090
Oh, wow!

28:08.125 --> 28:09.388
Well?

28:09.423 --> 28:11.324
Uh...

28:11.359 --> 28:14.228
unbridled awe doesn't seem
to do justice.

28:14.263 --> 28:15.900
But it is the best I've got.

28:15.935 --> 28:17.869
I told you.

28:17.904 --> 28:20.971
I mean, come on, it's not real.
I mean...

28:21.006 --> 28:23.908
I expect a really good
"Poem of the day" out of this.

28:23.943 --> 28:25.008
Consider it done.

28:28.882 --> 28:31.949
So when's the last time
you talked? You and your--

28:31.984 --> 28:34.149
Capture it quick
before it disappears.

28:34.184 --> 28:35.348
Come on. Chop, chop.

28:38.188 --> 28:41.860
<i>♪ A young, single guy</i>
<i>comes to Sicily ♪</i>

28:41.895 --> 28:43.796
Who said I was single?

28:43.831 --> 28:45.963
<i>♪ Black and white photo</i>
<i>in hand ♪</i>

28:45.998 --> 28:48.229
You know, it's really hard
for me to write
with all this musical--

28:48.264 --> 28:51.562
<i>♪ A beautiful,</i>
<i>mysterious woman ♪</i>

28:51.597 --> 28:56.105
<i>♪ Is painted against the lamp ♪</i>

28:56.140 --> 28:57.975
Wow, you are nosy.

28:58.010 --> 29:00.307
Nosy Josie,
that's what they call me.

29:00.342 --> 29:03.079
All right, well, Nosy Josie,
I think it looks like

29:03.114 --> 29:06.478
we both have things we'd prefer
not to talk about.

29:09.857 --> 29:11.549
To magical sunsets!

29:11.584 --> 29:13.320
Thank you for sharing it
with me.

29:13.355 --> 29:14.552
Cheers.

30:12.546 --> 30:13.446
Hal?

30:16.319 --> 30:17.219
Hal?

30:19.993 --> 30:21.058
Hal!

30:23.194 --> 30:25.623
Hal!

30:25.658 --> 30:26.998
-Hal!
-Oh, jeez.

30:27.033 --> 30:29.231
-Oh.
-Oh, my God!

30:29.266 --> 30:30.936
Oh, I am so sorry.

30:30.971 --> 30:32.399
Oh, my God.

30:32.434 --> 30:34.940
I think you just gave me
a heart attack.

30:34.975 --> 30:37.041
Um, okay.

30:37.076 --> 30:39.912
How about a little tutorial?

30:42.675 --> 30:45.676
Okay, so don't tamp the grounds.
Let them settle.

30:45.711 --> 30:48.250
Okay. Got it.

30:48.285 --> 30:49.614
Couldn't sleep?

30:49.649 --> 30:51.583
Literally the most
comfortable bed ever

30:51.618 --> 30:54.421
and I couldn't stay still.
My mind was just racing.

30:54.456 --> 30:57.655
-Uh, anyway, so just
screw this on here?
-Mm-hmm.

30:57.690 --> 31:00.031
-Okay.
-Okay

31:00.066 --> 31:02.099
Yeah, I know the feeling.

31:02.134 --> 31:05.135
Plus, I never heard
your sunset poem.

31:05.170 --> 31:07.940
So it didn't feel
quite right to go to sleep.

31:07.975 --> 31:09.370
Uh-huh. Sure.

31:09.405 --> 31:10.470
There we go.

31:10.505 --> 31:12.373
Okay. Good.

31:12.408 --> 31:14.276
Now you're gonna let
the water gurgle.

31:14.311 --> 31:16.377
It's gonna push--
steam's gonna push the water

31:16.412 --> 31:18.313
through the grounds to the top.

31:18.348 --> 31:20.678
And voila!

31:20.713 --> 31:22.515
-Science.
-Mm-hmm.

31:33.099 --> 31:35.495
The last time we spoke
was right before he left.

31:35.530 --> 31:37.365
No calls or texts since.

31:37.400 --> 31:38.300
Nothing.

31:40.304 --> 31:41.336
Are you okay?

31:41.371 --> 31:42.403
-I mean--

31:42.438 --> 31:43.701
It's a two-way street.

31:43.736 --> 31:46.638
I haven't exactly
reached out either.

31:46.673 --> 31:48.079
What did you guys fight about?

31:50.116 --> 31:51.676
Uh, well,
he brought up marriage,

31:51.711 --> 31:54.547
which to his credit,
we've been together for a years

31:54.582 --> 31:57.088
and that's something couples
should talk about, but...

31:57.123 --> 31:58.221
But?

31:58.256 --> 31:59.585
But every time he brings it up,

31:59.620 --> 32:02.126
I get so uncomfortable
and squirmy, and

32:02.161 --> 32:04.524
then he gets mad
and here we are.

32:04.559 --> 32:07.626
To cap it off,
his last gesture before he left.

32:07.661 --> 32:10.167
He slipped this on the counter
and went to Switzerland.

32:12.798 --> 32:14.303
Oh, wow.

32:14.338 --> 32:15.238
Yeah.

32:18.507 --> 32:20.276
-Do you love him?
-Of course I love him.

32:20.311 --> 32:22.047
Okay, then why did you
get uncomfortable?

32:22.082 --> 32:25.479
If I knew the answer
to that, I...

32:25.514 --> 32:28.119
-I don't think that--
-Sorry, sorry, sorry.

32:28.154 --> 32:29.516
No, it's fine.

32:29.551 --> 32:30.715
It's none of my business.

32:32.719 --> 32:34.224
There's something about
- 00 a.m. that makes

32:34.259 --> 32:36.061
the hard conversations easier.

32:37.757 --> 32:40.098
What about you?

32:40.133 --> 32:41.660
-Uh--
-You know, sometimes,

32:41.695 --> 32:43.233
it's good to get everything
off your chest.

32:43.268 --> 32:44.531
Uh, I put it on paper.

32:44.566 --> 32:47.402
-But if no one ever reads it?
-Stop...

32:47.437 --> 32:49.206
...making sense. Okay?

32:53.344 --> 32:55.344
Okay. Here we go.

32:55.379 --> 32:58.083
-How did we do?

32:58.118 --> 32:59.018
-Okay.
-Okay?

33:00.780 --> 33:03.616
-You know...
-Beautiful.

33:03.651 --> 33:06.124
This makes about
a quarter of the portion

33:06.159 --> 33:09.061
of the average size
in the United States.

33:09.096 --> 33:10.491
Remember,

33:10.526 --> 33:12.592
quality over quantity.

33:16.103 --> 33:19.401
Okay, I think it's about time
for that sunset poem.

33:19.436 --> 33:21.073
Nope. That's not any good.

33:21.108 --> 33:23.405
Oh, my gosh. Quit apologizing.
Just read it.

33:23.440 --> 33:25.374
Okay,
Ms. Back to the drawing board.

33:25.409 --> 33:26.672
That's different.

33:26.707 --> 33:29.609
-How's that different?
-It's different.

33:29.644 --> 33:31.413
Following up expectations,

33:31.448 --> 33:33.547
trying to write something
that people like.

33:33.582 --> 33:35.384
Seems like a great poem to have.

33:35.419 --> 33:37.452
You know what else
is a great poem to have?

33:37.487 --> 33:39.289
Being a talented writer.

33:39.324 --> 33:41.159
Okay, let's pump the brakes
on the whole writer thing.

33:41.194 --> 33:44.558
Being a talented writer
who just has to take a leap.

33:44.593 --> 33:47.396
Okay, so we both think
the other's talented.

33:47.431 --> 33:50.531
-Now what?
-Sunset poem.

33:50.566 --> 33:54.601
You're relentless.

33:59.377 --> 34:01.179
<i>"Perhaps it's that</i>
<i>twisted lemon,</i>

34:01.214 --> 34:03.313
<i>slice of heaven,</i>
<i>meringue fluff,</i>

34:03.348 --> 34:05.744
<i>with golden crusted</i>
<i>constellation crumbs</i>

34:05.779 --> 34:07.416
<i>or sherbet rays,</i>

34:07.451 --> 34:09.880
<i>the twilight souffle, who knows?</i>

34:09.915 --> 34:11.750
<i>Or perhaps the sigh</i>
<i>of the breeze</i>

34:11.785 --> 34:13.785
<i>pickpockets secrets</i>
<i>and tucks them in the clouds</i>

34:13.820 --> 34:15.655
<i>on their fly-by.</i>

34:15.690 --> 34:18.592
<i>Perhaps it's the hoodwinked</i>
<i>clairvoyant horizon</i>

34:18.627 --> 34:22.167
<i>that knows when one day comes</i>
<i>and another one goes.</i>

34:22.202 --> 34:25.203
<i>And perhaps the sun blows</i>
<i>kisses to the moon</i>
<i>as it departs,</i>

34:25.238 --> 34:27.799
<i>they work two separate shifts</i>
<i>with one beating heart.</i>

34:27.834 --> 34:29.636
<i>Perhaps.</i>

34:29.671 --> 34:32.705
<i>Perhaps the snoring mountain</i>
<i>turns in her sleep</i>

34:32.740 --> 34:36.511
<i>to dream in peace</i>
<i>or wish upon a star</i>

34:36.546 --> 34:40.383
<i>by the hecks of your hum</i>
<i>and the strum of your guitar.</i>

34:40.418 --> 34:41.417
<i>Perhaps."</i>

34:54.366 --> 34:55.926
Ow!

34:55.961 --> 34:57.895
What do you mean "ow?"
It's a pillow!

34:57.930 --> 34:59.897
I feel like
that's the general reaction

34:59.932 --> 35:01.239
when someone throws
something at you.

35:01.274 --> 35:03.637
Get up, sleepyhead.

35:03.672 --> 35:06.409
-What time is it?
-Just after- 00.

35:08.248 --> 35:10.248
Well, good news is I had
a perfectly comfortable bed

35:10.283 --> 35:13.515
about 20 feet away,
and didn't use it.

35:13.550 --> 35:14.945
Did you sleep out here too?

35:14.980 --> 35:16.617
Nope.

35:16.652 --> 35:18.157
Hey, you ever see
<i>The Godfather?</i>

35:20.326 --> 35:21.820
Have I seen<i> The Godfather?</i>

35:21.855 --> 35:23.327
What do I look like? An idiot?

35:23.362 --> 35:24.592
Okay, put some clothes on.

35:26.299 --> 35:28.266
-Quit hitting me.

35:41.347 --> 35:42.412
What are you--

35:44.680 --> 35:46.911
Ah. I see chivalry is not dead.

35:49.014 --> 35:51.520
What are you--

35:51.555 --> 35:53.324
-Oh, come on!

36:00.366 --> 36:01.728
So a few miles up the coast,

36:01.763 --> 36:03.598
there is this little town
called Savoca.

36:03.633 --> 36:05.534
It's where they filmed
some scenes from<i> The Godfather.</i>

36:05.569 --> 36:06.997
Oh, my brother's
gonna love that.

36:07.032 --> 36:08.834
He thinks I should be
seeing the Colosseum

36:08.869 --> 36:10.803
or touring some winery
and testing them.

36:10.838 --> 36:13.674
I mean, this place
has so many gems.

36:13.709 --> 36:14.807
So you have a brother?

36:14.842 --> 36:16.248
Yeah. Older.

36:16.283 --> 36:17.711
He has a family
and all that,

36:17.746 --> 36:19.581
my little niece, Stella.

36:19.616 --> 36:21.715
We actually run
the family print shop together.

36:21.750 --> 36:23.981
Look at you opening up.
We should road trip more often.

36:24.016 --> 36:26.852
Oh, hush, don't get used to it.

36:26.887 --> 36:28.293
Hey, you know it's rumored

36:28.328 --> 36:29.921
that Shakespeare
is from Messina.

36:29.956 --> 36:31.725
Oh, I know. It's part of
the reason I'm here.

36:31.760 --> 36:34.629
I think every writer knows that.

36:34.664 --> 36:36.433
Hal, I'd like to
point something out.

36:36.468 --> 36:37.929
You just called yourself
a writer.

36:40.703 --> 36:41.735
Mm.

36:50.482 --> 36:53.978
I present to you the location
of Michael Corleone's wedding.

36:54.013 --> 36:56.013
Oh, a little slice of history.

36:56.048 --> 36:57.784
To go with our pizza.

36:57.819 --> 36:59.522
-Works by the way.
-I know.

36:59.557 --> 37:01.557
Amazing.

37:01.592 --> 37:03.394
Hey, you know,
I got to tell ya, uh,

37:03.429 --> 37:05.825
I feel like this writer's
retreat is off to a great start.

37:05.860 --> 37:08.058
We're getting tons
of writing done.

37:08.093 --> 37:10.929
Inspiration is a part
of the process.

37:10.964 --> 37:13.899
-It's always good
to change up the scenery.
-Okay. Let me ask you this.

37:13.934 --> 37:16.341
-Mm-hmm.
-Since we aren't doing
much actual writing today.

37:16.376 --> 37:17.507
I beg to differ.

37:17.542 --> 37:18.871
-You're a folk singer.
-Mm-hmm.

37:18.906 --> 37:21.775
What exactly makes
a folk song a folk song?

37:21.810 --> 37:24.646
I mean, folk is kind of
a broad term, but

37:24.681 --> 37:27.077
folk songs are
songs of the people.

37:27.112 --> 37:28.749
You can debate genre,

37:28.784 --> 37:30.388
or even instrumentation,

37:30.423 --> 37:32.720
but I think a good folk song
tells a story.

37:32.755 --> 37:34.755
-Hmm. I like that.
-Mm-hmm.

37:36.660 --> 37:38.561
My turn.

37:38.596 --> 37:40.431
-For what?
-To ask a question.

37:40.466 --> 37:42.026
Oh, boy.

37:42.061 --> 37:44.061
The relationship is so lopsided.

37:44.096 --> 37:46.063
I don't know anything about you.

37:46.098 --> 37:48.340
That's not a question.

37:48.375 --> 37:50.507
Hal, I'm just-- I'm curious.

37:50.542 --> 37:53.807
Hey, listen, I told you
my whole life story
on the drive up here.

37:53.842 --> 37:56.040
You told me that
you had a brother.

37:56.075 --> 37:58.075
That barely scratches
the surface.

37:58.110 --> 38:00.946
-You are so demanding.
-Why are you in Taormina?

38:00.981 --> 38:04.114
Well, uh, we're not actually
in Taormina right now, so--

38:04.149 --> 38:06.050
-Why do you have to be
so difficult?

38:08.989 --> 38:12.463
Okay, you're right. But...

38:12.498 --> 38:14.927
-two stipulations. Okay?
-Okay.

38:14.962 --> 38:16.797
One.

38:16.832 --> 38:18.799
If I tell you, you have to
promise me something.

38:18.834 --> 38:19.899
-Okay.
-No, like promise.

38:19.934 --> 38:21.835
Okay, I promise. No

38:21.870 --> 38:24.772
sympathy at all. None.
Got it?

38:24.807 --> 38:26.543
-Okay.
-Okay.

38:26.578 --> 38:29.073
And two, since
we are in front of

38:29.108 --> 38:32.142
<i>The Godfather</i> landmark,
it only makes sense...

38:32.177 --> 38:34.452
that I get to do it
in my perfect Brando impression

38:34.487 --> 38:36.014
-that I know you
just love so much.
-No.

38:36.049 --> 38:38.555
-Nope. Absolutely not.
-Yep. It's the only way.

38:38.590 --> 38:39.490
No.

38:42.055 --> 38:44.726
Okay, fine.

38:44.761 --> 38:46.563
Well, that's--

38:50.932 --> 38:52.569
So...

38:52.604 --> 38:54.703
you may remember the woman
in the photograph.

38:54.738 --> 38:56.870
Right? The one you
helped me recreate?

38:56.905 --> 39:00.577
Well, you probably guessed it.
I mean, that's my mother.

39:00.612 --> 39:02.106
Right? And, uh...

39:02.141 --> 39:04.845
about two weeks ago,

39:04.880 --> 39:07.815
she died of cancer.

39:07.850 --> 39:09.454
And everybody who knew her said

39:09.489 --> 39:11.016
she was just made
of light, you know?

39:11.051 --> 39:12.952
I mean, she always had
the smile a mile wide

39:12.987 --> 39:16.923
and she was known
to just live for her children.

39:19.224 --> 39:22.434
She was the only one...

39:22.469 --> 39:25.162
that really gave me confidence,
especially in this stuff.

39:25.197 --> 39:26.900
Right? And, um...

39:29.234 --> 39:32.906
Anyway, so, she left us all
a bit of money, and...

39:32.941 --> 39:35.975
for me, she told me to do
something special,

39:36.010 --> 39:37.944
you know?
Something real meaningful.

39:37.979 --> 39:39.781
And that's a big pill
to swallow.

39:39.816 --> 39:41.717
So I...

39:41.752 --> 39:43.752
decided to come to her
favorite place in the world

39:43.787 --> 39:48.724
to figure out how best
to honor her legacy.

39:48.759 --> 39:50.561
And it's the first time
I've ever had any money.

39:50.596 --> 39:53.861
I didn't know what to do
with it, so...

39:53.896 --> 39:56.699
I figured I'd try to find
the answer here, you know?

39:59.099 --> 39:59.999
Sorry.

40:02.102 --> 40:04.168
-I am so sorry.
-No. No sympathy,

40:04.203 --> 40:06.643
-you promised.
-How will I not--

40:06.678 --> 40:10.779
I think my Brando
slipped into Mike Tyson
at the beginning there.

40:10.814 --> 40:12.484
How's your dad handling it?

40:12.519 --> 40:14.519
Well, depending on
what you believe,

40:14.554 --> 40:16.851
they've been reunited
as it were.

40:16.886 --> 40:18.655
So my brother and I,
we're orphans now.

40:21.594 --> 40:23.594
Wow. That's my first time
saying that out loud.

