43:03.250 --> 43:04.953
I like that.

43:04.988 --> 43:06.691
That's an old one.
That's not one of mine.

43:06.726 --> 43:08.825
But... it kinda
reminds me of you.

44:22.296 --> 44:25.264
I have successfully

44:25.299 --> 44:27.739
used the moka pot.

44:27.774 --> 44:29.235
You should be proud.

44:29.270 --> 44:31.006
-Okay.
-Nice.

44:32.339 --> 44:34.746
I think I've got something.

44:34.781 --> 44:36.473
What? No way.

44:36.508 --> 44:38.948
Oh, my gosh, you are not gonna
bail on me this time, are you?

44:38.983 --> 44:40.477
-Bail on you? Okay.
-Okay.

44:40.512 --> 44:42.281
Okay.

44:45.451 --> 44:47.154
Think of like a--

44:47.189 --> 44:49.486
-a train in the background.
-Okay.

44:51.556 --> 44:53.292
-Just do that the whole time.
-Okay.

44:53.327 --> 44:55.525
All right. Okay, I'm done.

44:55.560 --> 45:00.167
<i>♪ I can almost</i>
<i>hear them calling ♪</i>

45:00.202 --> 45:03.401
<i>♪ Out across the blue ♪</i>

45:06.846 --> 45:11.343
<i>♪ Three of them smiling</i>
<i>harbor views ♪</i>

45:13.886 --> 45:18.152
<i>♪ If I touch my skin</i>
<i>so lightly ♪</i>

45:18.187 --> 45:21.826
<i>♪ He is warm against me still ♪</i>

45:24.292 --> 45:27.293
<i>♪ Oh, it's long forgotten ♪</i>

45:27.328 --> 45:29.768
<i>♪ I've had my fill ♪</i>

45:31.871 --> 45:36.104
<i>♪ We learn about</i>
<i>a lot of things ♪</i>

45:36.139 --> 45:40.504
<i>♪ No one to pull me down ♪</i>

45:40.539 --> 45:45.179
<i>♪ All of my memories</i>
<i>How they haunt me ♪</i>

45:45.214 --> 45:48.281
<i>♪ Haunt me now, oh ♪</i>

46:04.035 --> 46:05.562
Have you had their pizzas
here yet?

46:05.597 --> 46:06.937
Mm-hmm.

46:08.204 --> 46:09.335
-Hello.
-Hello.

46:09.370 --> 46:11.271
<i>-Molto grazie.</i>
<i>-Prego.</i>

46:11.306 --> 46:12.976
Look at you speaking
in Italian in style.

46:13.011 --> 46:15.473
Oh, yeah, very impressive.
Practically fluent.

46:18.610 --> 46:19.983
-Mm-hmm. Yes.
-Both of you?

46:20.018 --> 46:21.116
Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

46:24.253 --> 46:28.354
Uh, sorry. You make
a beautiful couple.

46:28.389 --> 46:30.290
<i>Grazie.</i> We're actually
on our honeymoon.

46:30.325 --> 46:31.357
What? No?

46:31.392 --> 46:34.965
No, no, no. No.

46:35.000 --> 46:36.593
No, no. Uh, friends.

46:36.628 --> 46:38.496
-Uh, Amici.
-Yeah, amici.

46:38.531 --> 46:40.465
-What no say--
-Yeah, she actually,

46:40.500 --> 46:42.874
uh, she kidnapped me
and took me to her villa.

46:42.909 --> 46:44.205
It's kind of like
<i>Sunset Boulevard.</i>

46:44.240 --> 46:48.044
-I did not. He is crazy.

46:48.079 --> 46:51.179
Guys, there is such a,
you know,

46:51.214 --> 46:53.379
peace between you.

46:53.414 --> 46:56.514
You seem like friends to have
spent many years together.

46:56.549 --> 46:58.890
-We actually just met.
-Just a few days ago.

46:58.925 --> 47:01.222
No. First time here in Sicily?

47:01.257 --> 47:03.587
Uh, first time
leaving the States.

47:03.622 --> 47:06.128
Hal here, he's a pretty
impressive guy.

47:06.163 --> 47:08.966
He came all the way from-- Wait.

47:09.001 --> 47:11.430
-Where are you from?
-Okay, Iowa.

47:11.465 --> 47:13.234
Look at that.
Practically neighbors.

47:13.269 --> 47:15.434
Um, he came all the way
to Sicily

47:15.469 --> 47:17.535
from Iowa for inspiration.

47:17.570 --> 47:19.504
Um,<i> inspiracion?</i>

47:19.539 --> 47:22.210
Well, you seem
to have found it.

47:22.245 --> 47:24.014
Oh.

47:24.049 --> 47:26.445
Tony, here.

47:26.480 --> 47:29.184
We have a phrase for this.

47:29.219 --> 47:31.648
What you are doing.

47:31.683 --> 47:34.354
A leap of faith,
<i>salto mortale.</i>

47:34.389 --> 47:37.093
A leap of faith,
so they're artists.

47:37.128 --> 47:40.657
Ah, okay, I don't know if
that's the case with me.

47:40.692 --> 47:42.164
But she's the one.

47:42.199 --> 47:43.495
I mean, she's the one
who writes songs

47:43.530 --> 47:45.068
and then shares them
with the world.

47:45.103 --> 47:46.663
If anyone's brave,
it's definitely her.

47:46.698 --> 47:48.302
Mm. I think I am just lucky.

47:48.337 --> 47:51.140
Oh, let me go
to cook something

47:51.175 --> 47:54.011
for this nice couple.
They look hungry.

47:54.046 --> 47:55.375
<i>-Grazie.</i>
-Thank you.

47:58.182 --> 48:00.413
-Uh, my father. Sorry.

48:00.448 --> 48:02.382
It's okay.

48:02.417 --> 48:05.286
How about this? Simple.

48:05.321 --> 48:07.519
There is much beauty
in what you do.

48:07.554 --> 48:09.323
Both of you.

48:09.358 --> 48:11.490
<i>Molto Bella.</i>

48:11.525 --> 48:13.294
<i>-Grazie.</i>

48:16.662 --> 48:18.970
Oh, hon, don't forget.
We need to get one of those

48:19.005 --> 48:20.697
bottles of wine for your mom
before we go back.

48:20.732 --> 48:22.974
-Shut up.
It's your favorite.

48:23.009 --> 48:25.339
-We both know that.
-Stop.

48:25.374 --> 48:29.409
<i>♪ We learn about</i>
<i>a lot of things ♪</i>

48:29.444 --> 48:34.579
<i>♪ And no one</i>
<i>to pull me down ♪</i>

48:34.614 --> 48:39.254
<i>♪ And all of my memories</i>
<i>How they haunt me ♪</i>

48:39.289 --> 48:43.291
<i>♪ Haunt me now ♪</i>

48:43.326 --> 48:47.658
<i>♪ They all got so sick of me ♪</i>

48:47.693 --> 48:52.201
<i>♪ Wouldn't look at me</i>
<i>in the eye ♪</i>

48:52.236 --> 48:57.008
<i>♪ And all of my memories</i>
<i>How they haunt me ♪</i>

48:57.043 --> 48:59.604
<i>♪ Haunt me now ♪</i>

49:22.761 --> 49:24.464
Okay.

49:24.499 --> 49:26.103
If you don't think that's good,

49:26.138 --> 49:28.039
-you're officially insane.
-I don't know.

49:28.074 --> 49:29.469
No, come on.

49:29.504 --> 49:32.274
No, I don't know.
I don't know if it's like...

49:32.309 --> 49:35.145
fully honest or-- that might
not even be the right word.

49:35.180 --> 49:37.048
Wow, wow, look. I am an idiot

49:37.083 --> 49:39.380
when it comes to music,
but I know what I like.

49:39.415 --> 49:41.217
-You're biased.
-Who cares?

49:41.252 --> 49:42.548
I care. Do you know
how hard it is

49:42.583 --> 49:44.451
for musicians to write
a second record?

49:44.486 --> 49:46.090
Uh, no idea.

49:46.125 --> 49:47.784
But I'd, I'd like to think that,

49:47.819 --> 49:49.423
you know, maybe it has
something to do with them

49:49.458 --> 49:50.754
being too scared to follow up

49:50.789 --> 49:52.228
with something successful.

49:52.263 --> 49:53.658
Well, maybe it's
because they forgot

49:53.693 --> 49:55.165
why they even
started in the first place.

49:55.200 --> 49:56.496
Or what people connect with.

49:56.531 --> 49:57.827
I don't know. That just--

49:57.862 --> 49:59.829
that seems like
a recipe for misery.

49:59.864 --> 50:01.732
I'm gallivanting around Sicily,

50:01.767 --> 50:04.702
staying in this luxurious villa
and wasting time,

50:04.737 --> 50:06.209
who can relate to that?

50:06.244 --> 50:07.639
Hey, don't knock this villa.

50:07.674 --> 50:09.146
Someone once told me it's a
perfect place

50:09.181 --> 50:10.378
for a writer's retreat.

50:10.413 --> 50:11.742
Shut up.

50:11.777 --> 50:13.315
No, but I mean, come on,
all right. Let's--

50:13.350 --> 50:14.712
Let's go back a little bit.

50:14.747 --> 50:16.384
There's a--
there's a great quote, okay?

50:16.419 --> 50:18.452
Um, "Comparison is
the death of joy."

50:18.487 --> 50:19.585
-Mm-hmm.
-Right?

50:19.620 --> 50:20.850
So you gotta stop being so hard

50:20.885 --> 50:22.555
on yourself and comparing

50:22.590 --> 50:24.194
everything you do
to loving right.

50:24.229 --> 50:26.691
I mean, it's legitimately
a tiny fraction

50:26.726 --> 50:29.100
of what's going to be
a gargantuan career.

50:29.135 --> 50:30.530
-I don't know.
-I do.

50:30.565 --> 50:32.268
It's easy for you to say, Hal.

50:32.303 --> 50:34.600
Everything is so effortless
in that notebook.

50:34.635 --> 50:37.768
And then you're totally fine
with just keeping it
all to yourself.

50:37.803 --> 50:39.374
There's nothing wrong
with being unknown.

50:39.409 --> 50:41.079
But there is something wrong
with not trying.

50:43.248 --> 50:45.380
Writing makes me happy.

50:45.415 --> 50:47.415
If nobody reads it...

50:47.450 --> 50:49.351
Uh...

50:49.386 --> 50:52.387
Who said that?
Comparison is the death of joy.

50:52.422 --> 50:55.654
Probably Abe Lincoln
or Mark Twain.

50:55.689 --> 50:57.194
Did you fact-check that?

50:57.229 --> 50:59.295
I don't know.

50:59.330 --> 51:01.462
According to the internet,
they said everything.

51:09.472 --> 51:11.736
Ever stood on an active volcano?

51:11.771 --> 51:14.673
Nope. This would be
a first for me.

51:14.708 --> 51:16.411
Are you scared? Oh.

51:16.446 --> 51:18.578
-No, more impressed.

51:18.613 --> 51:20.481
I mean, isn't it crazy
to imagine the amount

51:20.516 --> 51:22.318
of destruction that thing
can cause?

51:22.353 --> 51:24.716
But it's just
sitting there, peacefully,

51:24.751 --> 51:27.818
biding its time
and growing wine.

51:27.853 --> 51:29.589
You know, if you look
over there,

51:29.624 --> 51:32.295
you can see the spot where
we had the perfect view

51:32.330 --> 51:33.857
of Etna. And now we're here.

51:33.892 --> 51:35.364
-It's weird how that works.
-Yeah.

51:35.399 --> 51:37.399
It's also weird that--
I keep thinking,

51:37.434 --> 51:38.829
weren't we supposed
to get bored today

51:38.864 --> 51:40.402
to get some
actual writing done?

51:40.437 --> 51:41.865
Mm. It's what I'm doing.

51:41.900 --> 51:43.438
How can you get bored
with all this around?

51:43.473 --> 51:44.637
I mean, you shout have
stayed in Minnesota

51:44.672 --> 51:45.869
or come visited me in Iowa.

51:45.904 --> 51:47.607
You'd definitely get bore there.

51:47.642 --> 51:49.840
-Did your parents
live there too? In Iowa?
-Mm.

51:52.383 --> 51:54.218
Did you get to spend time
with your mom

51:54.253 --> 51:56.187
before she passed?

51:56.222 --> 51:57.947
Whoa, look at that.
You see that?

51:57.982 --> 51:59.652
-What?
-That's the mood.

51:59.687 --> 52:02.391
It just died
'cause you killed it.

52:02.426 --> 52:06.329
Okay, Mr. Destructive Volcano.

52:06.364 --> 52:08.595
Yeah, I sat with her every day.

52:08.630 --> 52:09.860
Good talks?

52:09.895 --> 52:12.401
Sometimes.
Sometimes we'd just...

52:12.436 --> 52:14.898
sit in silence and...

52:14.933 --> 52:17.274
actually, I read her
a poem every day.

52:18.838 --> 52:21.245
We never had that
all revealing talk

52:21.280 --> 52:24.908
where she imparts
her wisdom on how to carry on
without her, but

52:24.943 --> 52:27.911
I will never forget the way
her hands looked.

52:27.946 --> 52:28.978
Mm.

52:29.013 --> 52:30.980
I can't imagine losing a parent.

52:31.015 --> 52:33.422
-Let alone both.
-Yeah.

52:33.457 --> 52:35.622
That's what I thought too,
but if there is any

52:35.657 --> 52:37.393
glimmer of positive thing,

52:37.428 --> 52:39.362
it's actually when I walked
into the funeral hall

52:39.397 --> 52:41.694
when I realized that...

52:41.729 --> 52:43.597
it brings us together as people.

52:43.632 --> 52:46.237
You know, all the petty stuff
goes out the window because

52:46.272 --> 52:48.899
we all lose loved ones. Um...

52:48.934 --> 52:52.309
we all face our own mortality.

52:52.344 --> 52:54.839
It kind of snapped life
into focus for a second.

52:56.744 --> 52:58.645
I just wish they...

52:58.680 --> 53:00.911
could've seen
their grandchildren
grow up, you know.

53:03.289 --> 53:07.588
We all want more time.
We don't appreciate
what we get, so it's...

53:07.623 --> 53:09.722
Wow, I'm so sorry
I dragged on there.

53:09.757 --> 53:12.560
Um, I'm sorry.

53:12.595 --> 53:14.760
You lose someone
close to you?

53:14.795 --> 53:16.696
Yeah. My grandpa.

53:16.731 --> 53:18.533
He was pretty magical.

53:18.568 --> 53:22.306
World traveler,
always curious and...

53:22.341 --> 53:24.539
he had this spark that, like,
not most people have.

53:26.477 --> 53:28.279
You kinda have it.

53:28.314 --> 53:30.809
Oh, I have a spark?
What does it look like?

53:30.844 --> 53:33.042
Shut up. It was a compliment.

53:33.077 --> 53:34.615
Jerk.

53:34.650 --> 53:35.715
No, seriously, though,

53:35.750 --> 53:36.947
he sounds like an amazing man.

53:36.982 --> 53:38.586
He was. Definitely something

53:38.621 --> 53:39.785
to aspire to, for sure.

54:19.464 --> 54:21.365
Hey, Josie. Um...

54:21.400 --> 54:22.762
Can you come out here,
I have an important question

54:22.797 --> 54:24.797
for you, please?

54:24.832 --> 54:26.370
About something I found.

54:29.573 --> 54:31.936
Yeah. I need you
to clear something up
for me really quick.

54:31.971 --> 54:36.479
What exactly makes
a love song...

54:36.514 --> 54:38.745
-obscure?
-No, no, no, no.

54:38.780 --> 54:40.516
-Put that down.
-Mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

54:40.551 --> 54:42.045
Oh, no, no, no.
We're definitely playing it.

54:42.080 --> 54:43.849
Oh, my gosh. It was
confusing times in college.

54:43.884 --> 54:45.521
Don't you play that.

54:45.556 --> 54:46.852
You know, this is amazing.

54:46.887 --> 54:48.656
Don't you dare
apologize for this.

54:48.691 --> 54:50.658
-My gosh.
-Uh-huh.

54:50.693 --> 54:52.792
And by the way, you look--

54:52.827 --> 54:53.760
What's the occasion?

54:53.795 --> 54:54.959
No, I just felt

54:54.994 --> 54:56.400
like dressing up.

54:56.435 --> 54:57.896
-Is that okay with you?
-Yeah.

54:57.931 --> 54:59.436
It's definitely okay.

54:59.471 --> 55:01.064
But I feel like
a lonely peasant.

55:01.099 --> 55:03.572
Well, it's our last night
to go out.

55:03.607 --> 55:04.870
I thought we had
tomorrow night.

55:04.905 --> 55:07.070
You have an early flight
the next morning.

55:10.108 --> 55:11.646
Well, I'll go get ready then.

55:11.681 --> 55:13.549
Until then, exclusive.

55:13.584 --> 55:17.619
<i>♪ Good night, my ladies ♪</i>

55:17.654 --> 55:20.523
Ooh, I like it.

55:20.558 --> 55:22.921
<i>♪ Good night, my ladies ♪</i>

55:22.956 --> 55:27.464
<i>♪ I am so sad</i>
<i>to see you go ♪</i>

55:29.765 --> 55:35.703
<i>♪ Merrily we roll along ♪</i>

55:38.510 --> 55:39.938
You clean up nice.

55:39.973 --> 55:41.379
Why, thank you.

55:43.009 --> 55:45.108
We're gonna dance to it.
Absolutely.

55:45.143 --> 55:47.451
There you go. There you go.

55:47.486 --> 55:50.652
-That right.
-Uh-huh.

55:50.687 --> 55:51.950
Very nice.

55:51.985 --> 55:53.589
Not too shabby.

55:57.628 --> 56:00.189
You do look beautiful.

56:00.224 --> 56:04.633
You also look beautiful.

56:04.668 --> 56:06.767
I do declare.

56:06.802 --> 56:09.506
-Okay. Let's go.

56:13.908 --> 56:19.582
<i>♪ Farewell, ladies ♪</i>

56:19.617 --> 56:23.751
<i>♪ Farewell, my ladies ♪</i>

56:23.786 --> 56:29.086
<i>♪ Oh, farewell, my ladies ♪</i>

56:29.121 --> 56:33.662
<i>♪ I am going to leave you now ♪</i>

56:35.765 --> 56:39.668
<i>♪ Merrily we roll along ♪</i>

56:41.606 --> 56:42.572
<i>♪ Merrily... ♪</i>

56:46.039 --> 56:47.841
We try so hard as musicians

56:47.876 --> 56:49.744
to put something good
into the world,

56:49.779 --> 56:51.548
and this is what people like.

56:51.583 --> 56:54.144
I can't believe Dean's brother
said he likes this place.

56:54.179 --> 56:55.486
You want to go somewhere else?

56:55.521 --> 56:57.587
Oh, no, no. It's fine.

56:57.622 --> 56:59.182
I am just being
a cranky old lady.

56:59.217 --> 57:00.854
Okay. How about this?
We do one drink

57:00.889 --> 57:02.592
-and then we'll leave.
-Okay.

57:02.627 --> 57:04.726
What drink do old ladies
drink around in these bars?

57:04.761 --> 57:06.860
Um, Camapri, neat.

57:06.895 --> 57:08.862
Okay, I'll make that two.

57:43.129 --> 57:46.097
Hey, Jo, this is Elizabeth
and Kenny.

57:46.132 --> 57:48.099
They're studying abroad in...

57:48.134 --> 57:49.540
-Florence.
-...Florence.

57:49.575 --> 57:50.970
And they heard about Taormina

57:51.005 --> 57:52.840
and wanted to come here
for the weekend.

57:52.875 --> 57:54.545
Art history majors.

57:54.580 --> 57:57.306
Yeah, they-- This is Josie Day,

57:57.341 --> 57:59.682
the famous musician.

57:59.717 --> 58:01.046
Oh!

58:01.081 --> 58:03.587
Oh, my God, no way.

58:03.622 --> 58:06.590
Hi. Josie, uh, not famous.

58:06.625 --> 58:09.219
Oh, Elizabeth. Like he said.

58:09.254 --> 58:11.221
-And you're Kenny, right?
-Yeah.

58:11.256 --> 58:13.597
You're sure it's okay
that we're with you?

58:13.632 --> 58:15.258
We're not interrupting
date night?

58:15.293 --> 58:16.963
Oh, no, you're totally fine.

58:16.998 --> 58:18.833
Okay.

58:18.868 --> 58:21.638
-So, Josie, what do you play?
-Uh, folk.

58:21.673 --> 58:23.640
Oh, also like country.

58:23.675 --> 58:27.171
Uh, no. Like Dylan.

58:27.206 --> 58:30.339
Cool! Cool!

58:30.374 --> 58:31.912
Yeah.

58:31.947 --> 58:34.079
You know, could I just say
it's so nice

58:34.114 --> 58:36.752
to run into some
fellow Americans here.

58:36.787 --> 58:38.919
Yeah, not too many
this time of year.

58:42.155 --> 58:43.187
Shots!

58:43.222 --> 58:44.694
Let's do shots.

58:44.729 --> 58:46.861
Shots?

58:49.800 --> 58:52.262
You know, like the best part
about living in Europe

58:52.297 --> 58:56.739
is that you can fly, like,
anywhere for dirt cheap.

58:56.774 --> 58:59.940
And, like, see all these
beautiful, hidden little gems.

58:59.975 --> 59:02.272
Yeah, this is
my first time overseas.

59:02.307 --> 59:03.647
Shut up. No way!

59:03.682 --> 59:04.978
Way.

59:05.013 --> 59:06.309
So this is, like, the--

59:06.344 --> 59:08.080
the only place
you've been in Europe?

59:08.115 --> 59:10.313
Yeah, he just said that.

59:10.348 --> 59:11.655
Guilty.

59:11.690 --> 59:14.625
Oh, my God, that is so cute!

59:14.660 --> 59:18.354
Okay, well,
you have to at least visit us
in Florence, right, Kenny?

59:18.389 --> 59:20.290
-Right, Kenny?
-Totally.

59:22.701 --> 59:24.096
What about you, Josie?

59:24.131 --> 59:25.900
I've been to a few places.

59:25.935 --> 59:27.671
What's been your favorite?

59:27.706 --> 59:30.003
I mean, honestly, as beautiful
as it is over here,

59:30.038 --> 59:31.972
one of my favorite places
to go--

59:32.007 --> 59:35.041
Oh, my God! I love this song.

59:35.076 --> 59:38.715
Come on, Hal.
Join me for a dance?

59:38.750 --> 59:41.080
Come on. You look like
you can dance.

59:41.115 --> 59:42.213
-Let's go.
-Okay.

59:42.248 --> 59:43.753
Come on.

59:53.160 --> 59:54.423
So you were saying?

59:54.458 --> 59:58.229
Uh, Coeur d'Alene, Idaho.
Never mind.

1:00:06.140 --> 1:00:08.877
So I take it you two
aren't together then?

1:00:08.912 --> 1:00:12.243
No. She's hot
but we're just friends.

1:00:12.278 --> 1:00:13.717
Cool.

1:00:17.789 --> 1:00:19.756
Kenny, it's been
an absolute pleasure,

1:00:19.791 --> 1:00:21.186
but I think I'm gonna go.

1:00:27.799 --> 1:00:29.293
Do you want me
to walk you home?

1:00:29.328 --> 1:00:31.999
Oh, no. No, thanks.

1:00:32.034 --> 1:00:33.099
Cool.

1:01:03.395 --> 1:01:06.231
<i>Hey, it's Dean.</i>
<i>Leave a message.</i>

1:01:12.140 --> 1:01:13.843
Hey, Kenny.

1:01:13.878 --> 1:01:17.044
Did, uh-- did Josie
go to the bathroom or what?

1:01:17.079 --> 1:01:19.849
Uh, unless the bathroom
is out the front door,

1:01:19.884 --> 1:01:20.982
I don't think so.

1:01:21.017 --> 1:01:22.181
Oh, shit.

1:01:22.216 --> 1:01:23.787
Oh, I should go.

1:01:23.822 --> 1:01:26.284
What? No. Come on,
we're having so much fun!

1:01:26.319 --> 1:01:28.451
No, I can't, I can't, I can't.

1:01:28.486 --> 1:01:31.993
All right, all right.
Well, just give me your phone.

1:01:32.028 --> 1:01:34.325
-Huh?
-I said give me your phone.

1:01:34.360 --> 1:01:36.767
Oh.

1:01:36.802 --> 1:01:38.362
-There you go.
-Thank you.

1:01:42.874 --> 1:01:45.402
Text me sometime
about Florence.

1:01:45.437 --> 1:01:46.843
Okay.

1:02:30.856 --> 1:02:33.252
I didn't think you were coming.

1:02:33.287 --> 1:02:35.551
I know.

1:02:35.586 --> 1:02:36.486
Sorry.

1:03:36.350 --> 1:03:37.514
Jose?

1:04:34.276 --> 1:04:36.672
Excuse me,<i> Signorina,</i>

1:04:36.707 --> 1:04:38.377
I hate to presume,

1:04:38.412 --> 1:04:41.644
but you seem like someone
who appreciates poetry.

1:04:41.679 --> 1:04:44.515
Mind if I share
a little something
that I concocted?

1:04:44.550 --> 1:04:48.024
Does it describe in detail
what Elizabeth's, uh,

1:04:48.059 --> 1:04:50.125
tongue felt like
down your throat or--?

1:04:50.160 --> 1:04:52.556
No, that would be
tomorrow's poem.

1:04:52.591 --> 1:04:53.458
Oh, yes.

1:04:55.264 --> 1:04:58.166
If you don't mind,
it's more a poem of the week.

1:04:58.201 --> 1:04:59.662
I guess I'll let that slide.

1:05:02.634 --> 1:05:04.403
It's called "Jokers."

1:05:06.572 --> 1:05:09.045
"I think time and space
are privy

1:05:09.080 --> 1:05:10.739
to the same inside joke
that fate

1:05:10.774 --> 1:05:12.675
has been telling for years.

1:05:12.710 --> 1:05:15.678
The punchline usually
involves my constant clear miss,

1:05:15.713 --> 1:05:18.516
or a wrong-call coin toss.

1:05:18.551 --> 1:05:21.354
It's on this little island
that they finally agree.

1:05:21.389 --> 1:05:22.718
Let's be kind for once,

1:05:22.753 --> 1:05:24.621
leave it up to the boy.

1:05:24.656 --> 1:05:26.260
Let's give it to him.

1:05:26.295 --> 1:05:28.625
Give him the melody
that summons the sea,

1:05:28.660 --> 1:05:30.066
or else he'll walk
a different path

1:05:30.101 --> 1:05:32.629
and so, so shall she.

1:05:32.664 --> 1:05:35.170
Give them the hours
times breath

1:05:35.205 --> 1:05:38.536
and cobblestone magic,
fate's embrace.

1:05:38.571 --> 1:05:40.472
Teach them<i> salto mortale,</i>

1:05:40.507 --> 1:05:41.407
that leap of faith."

1:05:44.082 --> 1:05:46.610
Okay, that was actually
pretty sweet.

1:05:46.645 --> 1:05:48.678
But I didn't ask
for you to come find me.

1:05:48.713 --> 1:05:51.186
Hey, you left a note.
Anyone who leaves a note
wants to be found.

1:05:51.221 --> 1:05:53.188
I'm trying to get bored.

1:05:53.223 --> 1:05:55.157
Okay, look,

1:05:55.192 --> 1:05:57.159
I get that you're upset.

1:05:57.194 --> 1:05:58.457
I'm not upset.

1:05:58.492 --> 1:06:00.129
There's nothing
to be upset about.

1:06:00.164 --> 1:06:02.098
Okay.

1:06:02.133 --> 1:06:04.067
Well,

1:06:04.102 --> 1:06:05.596
can we at least address
the obnoxiously

1:06:05.631 --> 1:06:07.202
large elephant in the room?

1:06:07.237 --> 1:06:09.072
We're not technically
in a room,

1:06:09.107 --> 1:06:11.305
we're actually in
an ancient garden.

1:06:11.340 --> 1:06:14.044
Okay, that's a very new way
of dodging things,

1:06:14.079 --> 1:06:16.112
but it's my last day
and I'm trying to apologize.

1:06:16.147 --> 1:06:18.543
I don't want things to be weird.

1:06:18.578 --> 1:06:20.347
What's the elephant in the room?

1:06:22.285 --> 1:06:24.681
The elephant,
let's call him Gustav,

1:06:24.716 --> 1:06:28.619
is that you're pissed
I hooked up with someone,

1:06:28.654 --> 1:06:31.589
which leads me
to believe that maybe,

1:06:31.624 --> 1:06:33.723
just maybe you share
the same feelings about me

1:06:33.758 --> 1:06:35.329
that I do about you.

1:06:37.102 --> 1:06:39.366
Okay, look.
Elizabeth may be tiny,

1:06:39.401 --> 1:06:40.664
but she packs a hell
of a punch.

1:06:40.699 --> 1:06:42.204
I mean, very forceful.

1:06:42.239 --> 1:06:44.140
No. No impersonations,
no grunts,

1:06:44.175 --> 1:06:46.802
no whatever it is you always do
to keep things light.

1:06:46.837 --> 1:06:48.375
Did you ever think for a minute

1:06:48.410 --> 1:06:51.081
that maybe that's not what
I'm upset about.

1:06:51.116 --> 1:06:53.116
Maybe I'm upset that
you have all this talent

1:06:53.151 --> 1:06:55.613
and you're gonna go back working
at a print shop in Iowa.

1:06:55.648 --> 1:06:57.483
Oh, okay, I have to pay
the bills, Jose.

1:06:57.518 --> 1:06:59.485
Plus, it's not like I'm just
gonna stop writing.

1:06:59.520 --> 1:07:02.323
What are you gonna do with
the rest of your mom's gift?

1:07:02.358 --> 1:07:04.556
I don't know. I'm still
figuring that out.

1:07:04.591 --> 1:07:07.295
Oh, my God, Hal,
it is so obvious.

1:07:09.893 --> 1:07:12.102
Take the money
to have time off,

1:07:12.137 --> 1:07:14.170
to invest in yourself,
to write a book.

1:07:14.205 --> 1:07:15.732
-I can't do that.
-Why not?

1:07:15.767 --> 1:07:18.075
Because it would be a waste
of her gift. Okay?

1:07:20.904 --> 1:07:22.277
Where are you going?

1:07:22.312 --> 1:07:23.575
You're too chickenshit

1:07:23.610 --> 1:07:25.148
to believe in yourself
and I was wrong.

1:07:25.183 --> 1:07:26.578
What-- About what?

1:07:26.613 --> 1:07:28.316
About you.

1:07:28.351 --> 1:07:30.450
Okay, hold on.
This coming from someone

1:07:30.485 --> 1:07:33.123
who's afraid to write a new song
because, what, she has one song

1:07:33.158 --> 1:07:35.323
that people like already?
It's a blip in your career.

1:07:35.358 --> 1:07:37.424
It's not like
you're trying to follow up
"Bohemian Rhapsody."

1:07:37.459 --> 1:07:39.690
At least I try, Hal.

1:07:39.725 --> 1:07:42.891
You're totally content
with never putting yourself
out into the world.

1:07:42.926 --> 1:07:44.530
And living under this guise

1:07:44.565 --> 1:07:46.400
of being some
"undiscovered" talent.

1:07:46.435 --> 1:07:48.567
Okay, maybe you're right.
Maybe I'm okay with that.

1:07:48.602 --> 1:07:51.603
But at least I confront
the real problems of my life.

1:07:51.638 --> 1:07:53.539
What is that supposed to mean?

1:07:53.574 --> 1:07:55.244
You're still with some guy

1:07:55.279 --> 1:07:57.312
who left on a work trip
to Switzerland

1:07:57.347 --> 1:07:58.907
after an epic argument,

1:07:58.942 --> 1:08:00.843
who you don't really
want to marry. I mean, come on,

1:08:00.878 --> 1:08:02.416
we, we have a phrase for this.

1:08:02.451 --> 1:08:03.747
It's called prolonging
the inevitable.

1:08:03.782 --> 1:08:06.156
-It is not that simple.
-It is.

1:08:06.191 --> 1:08:09.489
Leave him or be with him.
Pick one.

1:08:09.524 --> 1:08:12.162
You're just-- Okay, listen,
you're just stuck in this warp.

1:08:12.197 --> 1:08:13.493
Okay, this no man's land

1:08:13.528 --> 1:08:14.857
and you can easily
get out of it

1:08:14.892 --> 1:08:16.793
if you just make a decision.

1:08:16.828 --> 1:08:19.631
Here's a decision.
Pack your things
and go back to the hotel.

1:08:19.666 --> 1:08:21.402
This is too muddy.

1:08:21.437 --> 1:08:23.602
-But it's my last night.
-I know.

1:08:27.245 --> 1:08:29.212
You know what the worst part
about all this is?

1:08:29.247 --> 1:08:31.280
I can tell just by
the look on your face,

1:08:31.315 --> 1:08:32.644
you don't believe a word
of what you're saying.

1:09:36.809 --> 1:09:38.611
I'll...

1:09:38.646 --> 1:09:40.481
I'll, uh, I'll keep my ears open

1:09:40.516 --> 1:09:41.878
for that next hit song.

1:09:45.884 --> 1:09:47.917
You're not gonna need it,
but in case you need

1:09:47.952 --> 1:09:49.226
any concert apparel or...

1:09:58.028 --> 1:09:58.928
Well--

1:10:04.606 --> 1:10:05.506
Yeah.

1:10:10.678 --> 1:10:12.513
-Shit.
-What?

1:10:12.548 --> 1:10:14.614
-He's back early.
-Who, your boyfriend?

1:10:14.649 --> 1:10:16.451
-Obviously.
-Told you this was
a bad idea.

1:10:16.486 --> 1:10:18.816
-You have to go.
-No shit.

1:10:18.851 --> 1:10:20.521
You have to hide now!

1:10:20.556 --> 1:10:21.819
I'm not James Bond.
What are you--

1:10:21.854 --> 1:10:23.854
I don't care
who you are, just go!

1:10:23.889 --> 1:10:26.054
-Damn it.
-Go!

1:10:26.089 --> 1:10:27.330
-Oh, shit.
-Go!

1:10:34.735 --> 1:10:36.405
You scared me.

1:10:36.440 --> 1:10:38.308
I caught the early flight home.

1:10:38.343 --> 1:10:40.871
I can see that.

1:10:40.906 --> 1:10:44.479
Uh, I tried calling.

1:10:44.514 --> 1:10:45.546
I know.

1:10:47.550 --> 1:10:50.980
Do you want me to help you
with your bag?

1:10:51.015 --> 1:10:53.048
No, it's okay. Thanks.

1:11:09.407 --> 1:11:11.539
-Go.
-Where?

1:11:11.574 --> 1:11:14.542
This way!

1:11:14.577 --> 1:11:16.071
Quietly.

1:11:20.682 --> 1:11:21.714
Will I see you again?

1:11:21.749 --> 1:11:23.485
I don't know. Just go.

1:11:44.035 --> 1:11:50.072
<i>♪ He didn't seem to care</i>
<i>about my past ♪</i>

1:11:50.107 --> 1:11:51.777
How was Switzerland?

1:11:51.812 --> 1:11:54.043
<i>♪ I didn't ask him</i>
<i>much about... ♪</i>

1:11:54.078 --> 1:11:55.913
Exhausting.

1:11:55.948 --> 1:11:59.114
How are you?
Did you get much writing done?

1:11:59.149 --> 1:12:00.951
Not really.

1:12:00.986 --> 1:12:04.053
<i>♪ ...where it's cold</i>
<i>but I don't care ♪</i>

1:12:04.088 --> 1:12:07.122
<i>♪ We will show that we ♪</i>

1:12:09.126 --> 1:12:13.029
<i>♪ Were the clever ones ♪</i>

1:12:23.580 --> 1:12:25.074
Oh, almost forgot.

1:12:25.109 --> 1:12:29.078
<i>♪ The world breaks everyone ♪</i>

1:12:31.181 --> 1:12:32.554
Thanks.

1:12:32.589 --> 1:12:34.919
<i>♪ And afterwards I'm... ♪</i>

1:12:34.954 --> 1:12:36.525
I think I want to go
for a walk.

1:12:38.760 --> 1:12:41.530
I just got here.

1:12:41.565 --> 1:12:43.532
Don't you think we need
to talk about this?

1:12:43.567 --> 1:12:46.128
It's waited a week.
It could wait a few more hours.

1:12:49.606 --> 1:12:50.902
Thanks for the chocolates.

1:13:04.951 --> 1:13:10.658
<i>♪ And we would never</i>
<i>be happy like this ♪</i>

1:13:10.693 --> 1:13:13.122
<i>♪ Oh ♪</i>

